{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I want to take you on a trip"},{"time":2000,"text":"to an alien world."},{"time":5000,"text":"And it's not a trip"},{"time":7000,"text":"that requires light-years of travel,"},{"time":10000,"text":"but it's to a place"},{"time":12000,"text":"where it's defined by light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15000,"text":"So it's a little-appreciated fact"},{"time":18000,"text":"that most of the animals in our ocean"},{"time":23000,"text":"make light."},{"time":25000,"text":"I've spent most of my career"},{"time":27000,"text":"studying this phenomenon called bioluminescence."},{"time":30000,"text":"I study it because I think understanding it"},{"time":32000,"text":"is critical to understanding life in the ocean"},{"time":35000,"text":"where most bioluminescence occurs."},{"time":37000,"text":"I also use it as a tool"},{"time":39000,"text":"for visualizing and tracking pollution."},{"time":42000,"text":"But mostly I'm entranced by it."},{"time":45000,"text":"Since my my first dive in a deep-diving submersible,"},{"time":48000,"text":"when I went down and turned out the lights"},{"time":50000,"text":"and saw the fireworks displays,"},{"time":52000,"text":"I've been a bioluminescence junky."},{"time":55000,"text":"But I would come back from those dives"},{"time":58000,"text":"and try to share the experience with words,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and they were totally inadequate to the task."},{"time":65000,"text":"I needed some way to share the experience directly."},{"time":68000,"text":"And the first time I figured out that way"},{"time":70000,"text":"was in this little single-person submersible"},{"time":72000,"text":"called Deep Rover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"This next video clip,"},{"time":76000,"text":"you're going to see how we stimulated the bioluminescence."},{"time":78000,"text":"And the first thing you're going to see"},{"time":80000,"text":"is a transect screen"},{"time":82000,"text":"that is about a meter across."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: In front of the sub,"},{"time":86000,"text":"a mess screen will come into contact"},{"time":88000,"text":"with the soft-bodied creatures of the deep sea."},{"time":91000,"text":"With the sub's lights switched off,"},{"time":93000,"text":"it is possible to see their bioluminescence --"},{"time":96000,"text":"the light produced when they collide with the mesh."},{"time":105000,"text":"This is the first time"},{"time":107000,"text":"it has ever been recorded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"Edith Widder: So I recorded that with an intensified video camera"},{"time":124000,"text":"that has about the sensitivity"},{"time":126000,"text":"of the fully dark-adapted human eye."},{"time":128000,"text":"Which means that really is what you would see"},{"time":130000,"text":"if you took a dive in a submersible."},{"time":132000,"text":"But just to try to prove that fact to you,"},{"time":134000,"text":"I've brought along some bioluminescent plankton"},{"time":136000,"text":"in what is undoubtedly a foolhardy attempt"},{"time":138000,"text":"at a live demonstration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"So, if we could have the lights down"},{"time":144000,"text":"and have it as dark in here as possible,"},{"time":147000,"text":"I have a flask"},{"time":149000,"text":"that has bioluminescent plankton in it."},{"time":152000,"text":"And you'll note there's no light coming from them right now,"},{"time":155000,"text":"either because they're dead --"},{"time":157000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":159000,"text":"or because I need to stir them up in some way"},{"time":162000,"text":"for you to see what bioluminescence really looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"(Gasps)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"Oops. Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"I spend most of my time working in the dark; I'm used to that."},{"time":184000,"text":"Okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"So that light"},{"time":188000,"text":"was made by a bioluminescent dinoflagellate,"},{"time":191000,"text":"a single-celled alga."},{"time":193000,"text":"So why would a single-celled alga"},{"time":195000,"text":"need to be able to produce light?"},{"time":197000,"text":"Well, it uses it to defend itself from its predators."},{"time":200000,"text":"The flash is like a scream for help."},{"time":202000,"text":"It's what's known as a bioluminescent burglar alarm,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and just like the alarm on your car or your house,"},{"time":208000,"text":"it's meant to cast unwanted attention onto the intruder,"},{"time":211000,"text":"thereby either leading to his capture"},{"time":214000,"text":"or scaring him away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"There's a lot of animals that use this trick,"},{"time":218000,"text":"for example this black dragonfish."},{"time":220000,"text":"It's got a light organ under its eye."},{"time":222000,"text":"It's got a chin barbel."},{"time":224000,"text":"It's got a lot of other light organs you can't see, but you'll see in here in a minute."},{"time":227000,"text":"So we had to chase this in the submersible for quite sometime,"},{"time":231000,"text":"because the top speed of this fish is one knot,"},{"time":234000,"text":"which was the top speed of the submersible."},{"time":236000,"text":"But it was worth it,"},{"time":238000,"text":"because we caught it in a special capture device,"},{"time":240000,"text":"brought it up into the lab on the ship,"},{"time":242000,"text":"and then everything on this fish lights up."},{"time":245000,"text":"It's unbelievable."},{"time":247000,"text":"The light organs under the eyes are flashing."},{"time":249000,"text":"That chin barbel is flashing."},{"time":251000,"text":"It's got light organs on its belly that are flashing,"},{"time":253000,"text":"fin lights."},{"time":255000,"text":"It's a scream for help; it's meant to attract attention."},{"time":258000,"text":"It's phenomenal."},{"time":260000,"text":"And you normally don't get to see this"},{"time":262000,"text":"because we've exhausted the luminescence when we bring them up in nets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"There's other ways you can defend yourself with light."},{"time":269000,"text":"For example, this shrimp"},{"time":271000,"text":"releases its bioluminescent chemicals into the water"},{"time":274000,"text":"just the way a squid or an octopus would release an ink cloud."},{"time":277000,"text":"This blinds or distracts the predator."},{"time":280000,"text":"This little squid is called the fire shooter"},{"time":283000,"text":"because of its ability to do this."},{"time":285000,"text":"Now it may look like a tasty morsel,"},{"time":288000,"text":"or a pig's head with wings --"},{"time":290000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":293000,"text":"but if it's attacked,"},{"time":296000,"text":"it puts out a barrage of light --"},{"time":299000,"text":"in fact, a barrage of photon torpedoes."},{"time":303000,"text":"I just barely got the lights out in time"},{"time":305000,"text":"for you to be able to see those gobs of light"},{"time":307000,"text":"hitting the transect screen"},{"time":309000,"text":"and then just glowing."},{"time":311000,"text":"It's phenomenal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"So there's a lot of animals in the open ocean --"},{"time":317000,"text":"most of them that make light."},{"time":319000,"text":"And we have a pretty good idea, for most of them, why."},{"time":321000,"text":"They use it for finding food, for attracting mates,"},{"time":324000,"text":"for defending against predators."},{"time":326000,"text":"But when you get down to the bottom of the ocean,"},{"time":328000,"text":"that's where things get really strange."},{"time":331000,"text":"And some of these animals"},{"time":333000,"text":"are probably inspiration for the things you saw in \"Avatar,\""},{"time":336000,"text":"but you don't have to travel to Pandora to see them."},{"time":339000,"text":"They're things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"This is a golden coral, a bush."},{"time":343000,"text":"It grows very slowly."},{"time":345000,"text":"In fact, it's thought that some of these"},{"time":347000,"text":"are as much as 3,000 years old,"},{"time":349000,"text":"which is one reason that bottom trawling should not be allowed."},{"time":353000,"text":"The other reason is this amazing bush glows."},{"time":357000,"text":"So if you brush up against it,"},{"time":359000,"text":"any place you brushed against it,"},{"time":361000,"text":"you get this twinkling blue-green light"},{"time":364000,"text":"that's just breathtaking."},{"time":367000,"text":"And you see things like this."},{"time":369000,"text":"This looks like something out of a Dr. Seuss book --"},{"time":371000,"text":"just all manner of creatures all over this thing."},{"time":375000,"text":"And these are flytrap anemones."},{"time":378000,"text":"Now if you poke it, it pulls in its tentacles."},{"time":381000,"text":"But if you keep poking it,"},{"time":383000,"text":"it starts to produce light."},{"time":386000,"text":"And it actually ends up looking like a galaxy."},{"time":390000,"text":"It produces these strings of light,"},{"time":392000,"text":"presumably as some form of defense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"There are starfish that can make light."},{"time":398000,"text":"And there are brittle stars that produce bands of light"},{"time":401000,"text":"that dance along their arms."},{"time":404000,"text":"This looks like a plant,"},{"time":406000,"text":"but it's actually an animal."},{"time":408000,"text":"And it anchors itself in the sand"},{"time":410000,"text":"by blowing up a balloon on the end of its stock."},{"time":413000,"text":"So it can actually hold itself in very strong currents,"},{"time":415000,"text":"as you see here."},{"time":417000,"text":"But if we collect it very gently, and we bring it up into the lab"},{"time":420000,"text":"and just squeeze it at the base of the stock,"},{"time":423000,"text":"it produces this light"},{"time":425000,"text":"that propagates from stem to the plume,"},{"time":427000,"text":"changing color as it goes,"},{"time":430000,"text":"from green to blue."},{"time":433000,"text":"Colorization and sound effects"},{"time":435000,"text":"added for you viewing pleasure."},{"time":437000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":440000,"text":"But we have no idea why it does that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"Here's another one. This is also a sea pen."},{"time":444000,"text":"It's got a brittle star hitching a ride."},{"time":447000,"text":"It's a green saber of light."},{"time":449000,"text":"And like the one you just saw,"},{"time":451000,"text":"it can produce these as bands of light."},{"time":453000,"text":"So if I squeeze the base,"},{"time":455000,"text":"the bands go from base to tip."},{"time":459000,"text":"If I squeeze the tip, they go from tip to base."},{"time":465000,"text":"So what do you think happens if you squeeze it in the middle?"},{"time":469000,"text":"(Gasps)"},{"time":472000,"text":"I'd be very interested in your theories about what that's about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"So there's a language of light in the deep ocean,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and we're just beginning to understand it,"},{"time":482000,"text":"and one way we're going about that"},{"time":484000,"text":"is we're imitating a lot of these displays."},{"time":486000,"text":"This is an optical lure that I've used."},{"time":488000,"text":"We call it the electronic jellyfish."},{"time":490000,"text":"It's just 16 blue LEDs"},{"time":492000,"text":"that we can program to do different types of displays."},{"time":494000,"text":"And we view it with a camera system I developed called Eye-in-the-Sea"},{"time":497000,"text":"that uses far red light that's invisible to most animals,"},{"time":499000,"text":"so it's unobtrusive."},{"time":501000,"text":"So I just want to show you"},{"time":503000,"text":"some of the responses we've elicited"},{"time":505000,"text":"from animals in the deep sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"So the camera's black and white."},{"time":509000,"text":"It's not high-resolution."},{"time":511000,"text":"And what you're seeing here is a bait box"},{"time":513000,"text":"with a bunch of -- like the cockroaches of the ocean --"},{"time":516000,"text":"there are isopods all over it."},{"time":518000,"text":"And right in the front"},{"time":520000,"text":"is the electronic jellyfish."},{"time":522000,"text":"And when it starts flashing,"},{"time":524000,"text":"it's just going to be one of the LEDs that's flashing very fast."},{"time":527000,"text":"But as soon as it starts to flash --"},{"time":529000,"text":"and it's going to look big, because it blooms on the camera --"},{"time":531000,"text":"I want you to look right here."},{"time":533000,"text":"There's something small there that responds."},{"time":536000,"text":"We're talking to something."},{"time":538000,"text":"It looks like a little of string pearls basically --"},{"time":542000,"text":"in fact, three strings of pearls."},{"time":545000,"text":"And this was very consistent."},{"time":547000,"text":"This was in the Bahamas at about 2,000 feet."},{"time":549000,"text":"We basically have a chat room going on here,"},{"time":552000,"text":"because once it gets started, everybody's talking."},{"time":555000,"text":"And I think this is actually a shrimp"},{"time":557000,"text":"that's releasing its bioluminescent chemicals into the water."},{"time":560000,"text":"But the cool thing is, we're talking to it."},{"time":562000,"text":"We don't know what we're saying."},{"time":565000,"text":"Personally, I think it's something sexy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":569000,"text":"And then finally,"},{"time":571000,"text":"I want to show you some responses that we recorded"},{"time":573000,"text":"with the world's first deep-sea webcam,"},{"time":576000,"text":"which we had installed in Monterey Canyon last year."},{"time":578000,"text":"We've only just begun to analyze all of this data."},{"time":581000,"text":"This is going to be a glowing source first,"},{"time":584000,"text":"which is like bioluminescent bacteria."},{"time":586000,"text":"And it is an optical cue"},{"time":588000,"text":"that there's carrion on the bottom of the ocean."},{"time":591000,"text":"So this scavenger comes in,"},{"time":594000,"text":"which is a giant sixgill shark."},{"time":596000,"text":"And I can't claim for sure"},{"time":598000,"text":"that the optical source brought it in, because there's bait right there."},{"time":601000,"text":"But if it had been following the odor plume,"},{"time":603000,"text":"it would have come in from the other direction."},{"time":605000,"text":"And it does actually seem to be trying"},{"time":607000,"text":"to eat the electronic jellyfish."},{"time":610000,"text":"That's a 12-foot-long giant sixgill shark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614000,"text":"Okay, so this next one is from the webcam,"},{"time":617000,"text":"and it's going to be this pinwheel display."},{"time":620000,"text":"And this is a burglar alarm."},{"time":623000,"text":"And that was a Humboldt squid,"},{"time":625000,"text":"a juvenile Humboldt squid, about three feet long."},{"time":628000,"text":"This is at 3,000 feet in Monterey Canyon."},{"time":631000,"text":"But if it's a burglar alarm, you wouldn't expect it to attack the jellyfish directly."},{"time":634000,"text":"It's supposed to be attacking what's attacking the jellyfish."},{"time":637000,"text":"But we did see a bunch of responses like this."},{"time":640000,"text":"This guy is a little more contemplative."},{"time":643000,"text":"\"Hey, wait a minute."},{"time":645000,"text":"There's supposed to be something else there.\""},{"time":647000,"text":"He's thinking about it."},{"time":650000,"text":"But he's persistent."},{"time":652000,"text":"He keeps coming back."},{"time":654000,"text":"And then he goes away for a few seconds"},{"time":656000,"text":"to think about it some more,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and thinks,"},{"time":660000,"text":"\"Maybe if I come in from a different angle.\""},{"time":664000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":667000,"text":"Nope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669000,"text":"So we are starting to get a handle on this,"},{"time":672000,"text":"but only just the beginnings."},{"time":674000,"text":"We need more eyes on the process."},{"time":676000,"text":"So if any of you ever get a chance to take a dive in a submersible,"},{"time":679000,"text":"by all means, climb in and take the plunge."},{"time":682000,"text":"This is something that should be on everybody's bucket list,"},{"time":685000,"text":"because we live on an ocean planet."},{"time":689000,"text":"More than 90 percent, 99 percent,"},{"time":691000,"text":"of the living space on our planet"},{"time":694000,"text":"is ocean."},{"time":697000,"text":"It's a magical place"},{"time":700000,"text":"filled with breathtaking light shows"},{"time":708000,"text":"and bizarre and wondrous creatures,"},{"time":712000,"text":"alien life forms"},{"time":714000,"text":"that you don't have to travel to another planet to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"But if you do take the plunge,"},{"time":720000,"text":"please remember to turn out the lights."},{"time":723000,"text":"But I warn you,"},{"time":726000,"text":"it's addictive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}